            <p>Medical laboratory scientists provide physicians with information to detect disease or a predisposition to disease, confirm a diagnosis, and guide patient management.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cell small-12 medium-6 large-4">
            <img class="frame" src="../../images/img-row-2.jpg">
            <h2 class="h4">Emergency Health Sciences</h2>
            <p>Emergency Health Sciences provides paramedics an opportunity to advance their education by focusing on advanced medical care, EMS management and EMS education.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cell small-12 medium-6 large-4">
            <img class="frame" src="../../images/img-row-3.jpg">
            <h2 class="h4">Occupational Therapy</h2>
            <p>Occupational Therapists help people whose lives have been interrupted by accidents, illnesses, or congenital conditions build motor skills and cognitive and emotional functioning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cell small-12 medium-6 large-4">
            <img class="frame" src="../../images/img-row-4.jpg">
            <h2 class="h4">Physical Therapy</h2>
            <p>Physical therapists work most often with people with injuries, illnesses, or disabilities who need to improve their ability to move.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cell small-12 medium-6 large-4">
            <img class="frame" src="../../images/img-row-5.jpg">
            <h2 class="h4">Physician Assistant Studies</h2>
            <p>The Physician Assistant (PA) Studies program is one of only seven in the state of Texas and one of only two with a presence in South Texas, providing greater access to healthcare.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cell small-12 medium-6 large-4">
            <img class="frame" src="../../images/img-row-6.jpg">
            <h2 class="h4">Respiratory Care</h2>
            <p>Working closely with physicians and nurses, respiratory therapists perform critical diagnostic and treatment procedures for patients who must fight to breathe.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

